ed is $\\sim$10$^7$ kg,\ncorresponding to $\\sim$10$^{-5}$ of the nucleus mass. The observations are\nconsistent with partially shadowed sublimation from $\\sim$10$^4$ m$^2$ of ice,\ncorresponding to $\\sim$0.2\\% of the nucleus surface. For ice to survive in 313P\nfor billion-year timescales requires that the duty cycle for sublimation be\n$\\lesssim$10$^{-3}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 7 Jul 2015 22:39:35 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-08-26"}
